WHAT IS PUIC?
  Puding is a USB image creator for Pardus 2008 or later. You can write
  image to USB disk from any Pardus 2008 or later ISO image.

REQUIREMENTS
  python >= 2.5
  syslinux > 3.82.1
  mtools
  fuseiso
  fuse

INSTALLATION
  Now, puding is not stable and still it has not any graphical
  interface. So it is not at Pardus repositories, now. But you can
  package it your Pardus and install this package for using puic.
  Therefore:

  $ sudo pisi it puding

TRANSLATION
  For translators:
      $ cd $(PUDING)/po
      $ msginit -l $(LANG)

  For developers:
      $ cd $(PUDING)/po
      $ xgettext -f POTFILES.in -L Python --copyright-holder=GPLv3 --package-name=puding --package-version=TRUNK --msgid-bugs-address=gkmngrgn@gmail.com -o messages.pot

      $ cd $(PUDING)/qt4
      $ pylupdate4 /usr/lib/python*/site-packages/puding/qt*.py src/*.py -ts messages.ts
